---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Command Reference — aiConstitution">
  <section class="cs-prose">
    <p class="cs-section-label">CLI · v1.3.0</p>
    <h1>Command Reference</h1>
    <p>
      Every <code>ai</code> command runs against <code>~/.ai/</code> by
      default. Set <code>AI_ROOT=/path/to/dir</code> to redirect to a
      different directory — useful for testing without touching your live
      constitution.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ─── SETUP ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="cs-prose" style="margin-block-start: var(--space-16);">
    <h2>Setup &amp; Configuration</h2>

    <h3><code>ai setup</code></h3>
    <p>
      Reference-first guided setup. Shows that your constitution is already
      complete, then asks 8 personalisation questions (name, tools, cost
      ceiling, protected branches, behavioral style). Generates
      <code>Constitution.md</code>, installs hooks, and wires tool
      integrations.
    </p>
<pre><code>ai setup                        # interactive TUI
ai setup --non-interactive      # use wizard defaults
ai setup --no-hooks             # generate only — skip wiring</code></pre>

    <h3><code>ai compress [--wire]</code></h3>
    <p>
      Generates <code>Constitution.compact.md</code> (~5 KB, ~1,400 tokens)
      from the full <code>Constitution.md</code> (~38 KB). Contains every
      operative rule; strips rationale prose. Use <code>--wire</code> to
      switch <code>~/.claude/CLAUDE.md</code> to load the compact version.
    </p>
<pre><code>ai compress                     # generate compact version
ai compress --wire              # generate + activate in Claude Code
ai compress --output /tmp/c.md  # write to custom path</code></pre>
    <p>
      <strong>85% token reduction</strong> — the AI loads 1,400 tokens instead
      of 9,700 per session. Amend rules in <code>Constitution.md</code>, then
      re-run <code>ai compress</code>.
    </p>

    <h3><code>ai doctor</code></h3>
    <p>
      Runs a health check on the constitution tree. Prompts to install
      missing tools (e.g. <code>terminal-notifier</code>) rather than just
      warning.
    </p>
<pre><code>ai doctor</code></pre>

    <h3><code>ai status</code></h3>
    <p>Prints AI root path, constitution file presence, hook status, memory count, and recent audit activity.</p>
<pre><code>ai status</code></pre>
  </section>

  <!-- ─── CONSTITUTION ──────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="cs-prose" style="margin-block-start: var(--space-16);">
    <h2>Constitution Lifecycle</h2>

    <h3><code>ai constitution backup [--clear-links]</code></h3>
    <p>
      Archives all of <code>~/.ai/</code> to
      <code>~/.ai-backups/&lt;timestamp&gt;.tar.gz</code> — outside
      <code>~/.ai/</code> so restore doesn't overwrite it. Use
      <code>--clear-links</code> to also strip tool wiring after backup,
      leaving a clean session for testing a different constitution.
    </p>
<pre><code>ai constitution backup                # full archive
ai constitution backup --clear-links  # archive + clear wiring</code></pre>

    <h3><code>ai constitution restore [backup-id]</code></h3>
    <p>
      Removes current <code>~/.ai/</code> and extracts the latest (or
      specified) backup. Re-installs hooks, rewires
      <code>~/.claude/settings.json</code>, restores
      <code>CLAUDE.md</code> @-include, recreates the Copilot symlink,
      and regenerates <code>Constitution.runtime.md</code>.
    </p>
<pre><code>ai constitution restore               # restore most recent backup
ai constitution restore 20260525T120000Z  # restore specific backup</code></pre>

    <h3><code>ai migrate</code></h3>
    <p>
      Migrates a legacy four-file layout to the unified
      <code>Constitution.md</code> format. Run the three steps in order.
    </p>
<pre><code>ai migrate --flatten           # merge four files → one Constitution.md
ai migrate --add-behavioral    # insert §2 Behavioral Standards section
ai migrate --generate-runtime  # write Constitution.runtime.md</code></pre>

    <h3><code>ai generate runtime</code></h3>
    <p>
      Regenerates <code>Constitution.runtime.md</code> (the ~7 KB compact
      extract for Copilot CLI and Cursor) from the current
      <code>Constitution.md</code>.
    </p>
<pre><code>ai generate runtime</code></pre>
  </section>

  <!-- ─── AMENDMENTS ───────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="cs-prose" style="margin-block-start: var(--space-16);">
    <h2>Amendments</h2>
    <p>
      The amendment lifecycle: violation → draft stub → human edit →
      apply to constitution → bump version → re-compress.
    </p>

    <h3><code>ai amend draft &lt;violation-file&gt;</code></h3>
    <p>
      Reads a violation markdown file, extracts the rule reference and
      proposed amendment, and writes a draft stub to
      <code>~/.ai/governance/plans/&lt;timestamp&gt;-&lt;slug&gt;.md</code>.
      Opens the stub in <code>$EDITOR</code> if set.
    </p>
<pre><code>ai amend draft ~/.ai/audit/violations/20260525T120000Z-worktree.md</code></pre>

    <h3><code>ai amend apply &lt;draft&gt;</code></h3>
    <p>
      Patches the target section in <code>Constitution.md</code>, bumps
      the version, appends a changelog entry, and regenerates the compact
      runtime.
    </p>
<pre><code>ai amend apply ~/.ai/governance/plans/20260525T120000Z-worktree.md</code></pre>

    <h3><code>ai amend list</code> / <code>ai amend show &lt;slug&gt;</code></h3>
<pre><code>ai amend list                   # list drafts newest-first
ai amend show worktree-slug     # cat a specific draft</code></pre>

    <h3><code>ai review --check</code></h3>
    <p>
      Runs a 4-scan governance review: violations, overrides, drift
      records, and dead rules. Writes a dated report to
      <code>~/.ai/governance/reports/YYYY-MM-DD.md</code>.
    </p>
<pre><code>ai review --check</code></pre>
  </section>

  <!-- ─── HOOKS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="cs-prose" style="margin-block-start: var(--space-16);">
    <h2>Hooks</h2>

    <h3><code>ai hooks install [--copilot]</code></h3>
    <p>
      Extracts embedded hook scripts to <code>~/.ai/hooks/</code> and wires
      them into <code>~/.claude/settings.json</code>. The
      <code>--copilot</code> flag also creates the
      <code>~/.copilot/instructions/constitution.md</code> symlink.
    </p>
<pre><code>ai hooks install               # install all hooks
ai hooks install --copilot     # also wire Copilot CLI symlink</code></pre>

    <h3><code>ai hooks validate</code> / <code>ai hooks evaluate</code></h3>
<pre><code>ai hooks validate   # lint hook scripts (shebang, syntax, bare-except)
ai hooks evaluate   # run each hook with a synthetic event; assert non-crash</code></pre>
  </section>

  <!-- ─── SKILLS / PLUGINS / ATOMS ─────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="cs-prose" style="margin-block-start: var(--space-16);">
    <h2>Skills, Plugins &amp; Atoms</h2>

    <h3><code>ai skills</code></h3>
<pre><code>ai skills list                     # table of installed skills + descriptions
ai skills show &lt;name&gt;              # cat a skill's SKILL.md
ai skills validate                 # check each skill dir has valid SKILL.md
ai skills templates list &lt;skill&gt;  # list template files
ai skills templates show &lt;skill&gt; &lt;template&gt;  # render with variable substitution</code></pre>

    <h3><code>ai plugins</code></h3>
<pre><code>ai plugins install &lt;name[@version]&gt;  # install from plugin-atoms.com
ai plugins install &lt;url-or-path&gt;     # install from URL or local file
ai plugins status                     # list installed plugins
ai plugins enable &lt;name&gt;             # add to active set
ai plugins disable &lt;name&gt;            # remove from active set
ai plugins update &lt;name&gt;             # re-fetch from source URL</code></pre>
    <p>
      Bare names resolve to
      <code>https://plugin-atoms.com/&lt;name&gt;/&lt;version&gt;/plugin.tar.gz</code>.
    </p>

    <h3><code>ai atoms</code></h3>
<pre><code>ai atoms fetch &lt;name[@version]&gt;  # download from constitution-atoms.com
ai atoms fork &lt;name&gt; [--as &lt;local-name&gt;]  # local working copy
ai atoms publish --dry-run       # preview publication (full publish: coming soon)
ai atoms list                    # enumerate installed atoms</code></pre>

    <h3><code>ai op</code> — 1Password integration</h3>
<pre><code>ai op env                    # print KEY=op://vault/item/field lines
ai op signin                 # sign in to 1Password
ai op signout                # sign out
ai op whoami                 # show current account
ai op clip &lt;op://ref&gt;       # copy secret to clipboard (never prints value)</code></pre>
  </section>

  <!-- ─── IDENTITY / MODE ───────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="cs-prose" style="margin-block-start: var(--space-16);">
    <h2>Identity &amp; Mode</h2>

<pre><code>ai profile list/show/new/edit/remove  # manage persona profiles
ai persona list [--type agentic|reviewer]  # list installed personas
ai persona show &lt;name&gt;               # cat persona file
ai pm-mode                            # activate plan-first discipline
ai spawn &lt;persona&gt;                   # activate a sub-persona in current session
ai mode list/current/clear            # inspect and clear active mode</code></pre>
  </section>

  <!-- ─── PORTABILITY ──────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="cs-prose" style="margin-block-start: var(--space-16);">
    <h2>Portability</h2>

<pre><code>ai backup                    # snapshot ~/.ai/ to ~/.config/aiConstitution/backups/
ai sync push                 # push ~/.ai/ to configured git remote
ai sync pull                 # pull from remote
ai restore &lt;snapshot&gt;       # restore from snapshot
ai init                      # scaffold project.yaml + AI tool integration files
ai init --cursor             # write .cursor/rules/constitution.md symlink
ai init --codex              # write AGENTS.md with @-include</code></pre>
  </section>

  <!-- ─── NOTIFICATIONS ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="cs-prose" style="margin-block-start: var(--space-16);">
    <h2>Notifications</h2>
    <p>
      The <code>notify-me</code> script (installed by
      <code>ai hooks install command-wrappers</code>) sends desktop
      notifications when AI tasks complete.
    </p>
<pre><code>notify-me --title "Done" --message "Build finished" --level info
notify-me --title "Failed" --message "Tests failed" --level urgent
# --level urgent also pushes to ntfy.sh if ntfy_topic is set in settings.toml</code></pre>
  </section>

  <!-- ─── FULL REFERENCE ───────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="cs-prose" style="margin-block-start: var(--space-16);">
    <h2>Every flag</h2>
    <p>
      Run <code>ai &lt;command&gt; --help</code> for the full flag list.
      The top-level <code>ai --help</code> lists all commands.
    </p>
<pre><code>ai --help
ai setup --help
ai compress --help
ai constitution --help</code></pre>
  </section>
</Base>
